The problem of planarity testing is a classic topic in computational geometry, which falls under the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) category. The paper also involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic techniques, which could place it in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) categories. Finally, the use of bit manipulation and other optimization techniques could suggest that the paper belongs to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category.
